column23:
Hackathons are good. But a short burst (less than a day) of working is the ideal. More than that and we're probably working on a hard theme.

Exceptions: game jams. These are also hackathons but usually consists of more than one discipline (e.g. graphics, sound, game design, programming, etc). It might be open to debate if game jams are considered hackathons, but in my opinion, they are.

column23:
Game Jams

I think it's odd that game jams makes you come up with game ideas in such a short time when I spend ever day otherwise hardly coming up with anything.

I think it's the excitement and camaraderie that jump starts your brain to come up with amazing ideas in such a short time, and having the motivation to finish something within the tight deadline.

In this way it's a nice opportunity to join game jams to come up with more game prototypes when you need some. But doing it too frequently will upset your health and sleep schedule.
